Hi i'm moparclient and i'm about to teatch you how to add a 100% working poison system, i used rs as my base, thanks my friend for poisoning me :D

So lets start off !

[b]Step 1:[/b]
Declare this:
[code]public int poisondmge = 0;
public int poisonhit = 4;
public void poison() {
EventManager.getSingleton().addEvent( new Event() {
                    public void execute(EventContainer c) {
if (poisondmge > 0) {
poisonhit --;
poisonDmg = true;
dealDamage(poisondmge);
hitDiff = poisondmge;
updateRequired = true;
hitUpdateRequired = true;
if(poisonhit == 0)
{
poisondmge --;
poisonhit = 4;
}
   		   } else {
		   	  c.stop();
			}
                    }
                }, 18000);
}[/code]

So, thats is the poisoning system itselfs, if you want to poison someone, simply call the void poison(); and set the poison damage by using poisondmge int. 

Example:
[code]
if(poisondmge == 0){
sM("You have been poisoned!");
poison();
poisondmge = 6;
}[/code]
Close and save Client.java

[b]Step 2:[/b]

Open Player.java.

If you don't have, declare:
[code]public boolean poisonDmg = false;[/code]

Done that, seach for:
[code]protected void appendHitUpdate(stream str)[/code]

Under:
[code]
			if(hitDiff > 0 && healUpdateRequired && poisonDmg == false){
				str.writeByteA(0);
[/code]

Add:
[code]
			} else if (hitDiff > 0 && poisonDmg == true) {
				str.writeByteA(2);
				poisonDmg = false;[/code]

That will make the splat green.

And thats it ! if you want you can make it save the poisondmge int and on login it calls the void so it will continue hitting even if the player logged.

